item.title: CVE-2016-8609|2024-08-06T02:27:41.009Z -- red%20hat -- keycloak
item.description: It was found that the keycloak before 2.3.0 did not implement authentication flow correctly. An attacker could use this flaw to construct a phishing URL, from which he could hijack the user's session. This could lead to information disclosure, or permit further possible attacks.
